reviews.review_text:
Miller Gold Nice SBD given to us by the man, myth, legend. Nice sound. Performance in first set is tight, with a Bird Song that has some dark lines, and a nice peak.
The China-Rider cooks at a nice pace, and the He's Gone jam contains hints of the Other One, and the post drums Truckin. No post drums Jer ballad. I prefer Fall 84 to Summer, but this is a good listen, and a good Miller.

Phil is having fun see Minglewood for Phil bombs....

a little bit of hiss but the bass is definitely there

I loved expo and have always liked this show

thanks charlie
6-10-84 Nice show. Very good Phil heavy remaster by Charlie. Thanks Joani, Paul and Charlie.
Of course,I was there! Thank you tapers.Thank you Charlie Miller.Listen loud & #dontletgo
